encryption, privacy, and government secrecy, has received two weeks'
notice from Verio that its service will be terminated for unspecified
"violation of [its] Acceptable Use Policy." Cryptome has a history of
making publicly available documents and information that governments
would rather keep secret. For the notice, and a public response by
Cryptome webmaster John Young, see [2]Cryptome Shutdown by Verio/NTT."

