| Kaleidescape Triumphant in Court Case, DVD Ripping Ruled Legal     |
|   from the only-when-you-own-it-netflixers dept.                   |
|   posted by Zonk on Sunday April 29, @16:15 (Movies)               |
|   http://yro.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/29/1913251          |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]Jim Buzbee writes "Ever wanted to rip all your DVDs to a big network
server so that you could select and play them back to your TV? Up until
now, manufacturers have been wary of building a device to allow this type
of usage because they've been afraid a lawsuit. The DVD Copy Control
Association had claimed this was contractually forbidden, but now [1]a
judge says otherwise stating, 'nothing in the agreement prevents you from
making copies of DVDs. Nothing requires that a DVD be present during
playback.' Kaleidescape has finally won their long-standing lawsuit, a
case [2]we first talked about early in 2005."

