| Show Office 2007 Who's the Boss                                    |
|   from the not-tony-danza dept.                                    |
|   posted by Zonk on Sunday April 29, @17:25 (Microsoft)            |
|   http://slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/29/2038200              |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

jcatcw writes "Microsoft knows how you like your Office Suite. You like
Ribbons ... they're a given, right? Well, if not, [0]Computerworld
reviews some third-party packages that allow you to customize the
software's interface. [1]Classic Menu gives you an Office-2003-like set
of menus. It'll help you navigate old menu structures to find favorite
commands, but don't expect to use all the familiar keyboard shortcuts.
[2]ToolbarToggle lets you customize the menus. However, Classic Menu has
two advantages over ToolbarToggle: It's available for PowerPoint today,
and it includes Office 2007 commands on its menus, a modification you
can't make to ToolbarToggle menus. [3]RibbonCustomizer works within the
Ribbon's own constraints to let you change the display of icons and
commands on existing tabs or any new ones you create."

Discuss this story at:
    http://slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/04/29/2038200

