+--------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Dell Rethinking the Direct-Sales Market                            |
|   from the breaking-with-tradition dept.                           |
|   posted by Zonk on Sunday April 29, @19:29 (Businesses)           |
|   http://hardware.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/29/170208      |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

Dell has always sold directly to consumers via their web site and phone
operations; it's a basic element of their business. Chairman and chief
executive Michael Dell is now conceding that the company may need to
rethink basic practices by [0]considering alternative methods of selling
their products. While initially no specifics are given, the thought seems
to be than eventually the company will begin working with a retail chain.
"Dell's direct model came under pressure as the market for PCs shifted to
notebooks from desktops last year. It is harder to custom configure
notebook computers, so they had to be manufactured in advance, which lost
Dell some of its cost advantage. In addition, consumers were showing a
preference for touching and feeling a notebook PC before buying it."

Discuss this story at:
    http://hardware.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/04/29/170208

Links:
    0. http://www.nytimes.com/2007/04/28/technology/28dell.html?ref=technology



